The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Bengal | Tea takes blow
                                                                                                                     4                                                                                      Tea takes blow
                              An uprooted tree that smashed through the tin roof of a house. Picture by Anirban Choudhury                             
	April 14: Dooars gardens lost around two lakh kilos of tea leaves and had trees that shade tea plants flattened last night.         
	At least 2,000 houses were damaged and 10 people injured by hailstones during a storm that struck Kalchini in Jalpaiguri district around 8.30pm.         
	Four people were killed in Cooch Behar when their car rammed into a tree amid torrential rain this morning. Traffic on the highway that connects India with Bhutan remained stalled till late today as scores of uprooted trees lay across the road.                                                                                                                                                             
